articles.author: Omar Sohail
articles.title: Snapdragon 8 Gen 5’s AnTuTu Results Are Just A Tier Below The Snapdragon 8 Elite Gen 5, Highlighting Qualcomm’s Incredible Progress With Non-Flagship SoCs - Wccftech
articles.description: The first AnTuTu results of the Snapdragon 8 Gen 5 are here, and the fact that it performs just slightly slower than the Snapdragon 8 Elite Gen 5 is downright impressive
articles.content: Qualcomm is set to take the wraps off its Snapdragon 8 Gen 5 on November 26, with the chipset said to share the same 3nm N3P lithography as the Snapdragon 8 Elite Gen 5, but arrive with a few changes… [+1939 chars]
